---
/*
  VelaBench submission spec — the page external teams read before
  building a candidate. Kept as a single readable document; the
  authoritative source of truth is `vela bench --help` and
  `crates/vela-protocol/src/benchmark.rs`.
*/

import Page from "../../layouts/Page.astro";
import { HUB_URL, REPO_URL, FRONTIER, VERSION } from "../../config";
import { loadLeaderboard } from "../../lib/bench";

const leaderboard = loadLeaderboard();
---

<Page
  title={`Submit to VelaBench · ${FRONTIER.name}`}
  description="The submission spec for the Alzheimer's Therapeutics leaderboard. File format, scoring, edge-case handling."
  active="bench"
  eyebrow="VelaBench · submit"
  pageTitle="Submit to VelaBench"
  subtitle="Build a signed frontier; we score it; the leaderboard updates."
>
  <div slot="aside">
    <a href="/bench" class="aside-link">← leaderboard</a>
    <span class="aside-version">v{VERSION}</span>
  </div>

  <section class="spec-section">
    <h2 class="spec-section__title">What you submit</h2>
    <p class="spec-text">
      A single signed Vela frontier file (<code>.json</code>) covering Alzheimer's drug-target,
      mechanism, BBB-delivery, or clinical-readout claims. The frontier passes
      <code>vela check --strict</code> on its own — schema-valid, content-addressed, signed by an
      Ed25519 actor registered in the manifest.
    </p>
    <p class="spec-text">
      Build the frontier however you like:
      hand-curate it, run an LLM pipeline, port from an existing knowledge base, glue together
      paper extractions. The leaderboard doesn't care how the findings were produced — only
      that they cite primary literature with resolvable DOIs/PMIDs and that the manifest is
      cryptographically signed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-section">
    <h2 class="spec-section__title">How we score</h2>
    <p class="spec-text">
      Your frontier is matched claim-by-claim against the canonical
      gold ({leaderboard.gold.claims} signed claims, vfr_id <code>{leaderboard.gold.vfr_id}</code>).
      Matching is text + entity similarity, not exact-string equality. For each gold claim
      that finds a candidate, we count it as matched. For each candidate claim that finds
      no gold, we count it as a novel claim.
    </p>

    <table class="spec-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Metric</th>
          <th>Definition</th>
          <th>Weight</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>F1</code></td>
          <td>Harmonic mean of precision and recall over claim matches.</td>
          <td>0.50</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>entity_accuracy</code></td>
          <td>For each matched claim, fraction of gold's entities your claim also names.</td>
          <td>0.20</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>assertion_type_accuracy</code></td>
          <td>Fraction of matches where the assertion-type label agrees (mechanism vs therapeutic vs diagnostic, etc.).</td>
          <td>0.20</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>confidence_calibration</code></td>
          <td>Fraction of matches where your confidence score lands in gold's expected range (±0.15 around the canonical score).</td>
          <td>0.10</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="spec-text">
      Composite is the weighted blend; that's the headline number on the leaderboard.
      Reports also include exact-id matches (a stronger signal than text similarity),
      unmatched-frontier (your claims that didn't match gold — possibly novel), and
      unmatched-gold (gold claims you missed).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-section">
    <h2 class="spec-section__title">Reproduce the canonical run</h2>
    <pre class="spec-cmd">
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">git clone</span> {REPO_URL}
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">cargo build</span> --release -p vela-cli
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela registry pull</span> {leaderboard.gold.vfr_id} --from {HUB_URL}/entries --out gold-frontier.json
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela bench</span> ./your-candidate.json --gold benchmarks/gold-alzheimers.json --json
</pre>
    <p class="spec-text">
      The gold-claims file at <code>benchmarks/gold-alzheimers.json</code> is derived
      deterministically from the canonical frontier; rebuild it from a freshly-pulled
      <code>gold-frontier.json</code> using the converter at
      <code>scripts/gold-from-frontier.py</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-section">
    <h2 class="spec-section__title">Submit</h2>
    <p class="spec-text">
      v0.31 ships PR-based submissions. Land your candidate at
      <code>frontiers/&lt;your-id&gt;.json</code> with a one-line entry in
      <code>benchmarks/leaderboard.json</code>. CI runs <code>vela bench</code> and
      writes <code>benchmarks/results/&lt;your-id&gt;.json</code> on merge.
    </p>
    <p class="spec-text">
      v0.32 will accept submissions through a hosted endpoint —
      <code>POST /bench/submit</code> with a signed manifest pointer — so you don't need a
      PR for an automated agent run. The scoring engine is the same binary either way.
    </p>
    <p class="spec-text">
      Until the hosted endpoint lands, ship a PR and we'll merge promptly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-section">
    <h2 class="spec-section__title">Scope</h2>
    <p class="spec-text">
      The Alzheimer's Therapeutics suite covers six drug targets (Aβ, BACE1, tau,
      TREM2, ApoE, BBB delivery), four named clinical trials (lecanemab, donanemab,
      verubecestat, atabecestat), and the field-level contradictions surfaced from
      curator notes.
    </p>
    <p class="spec-text">
      Out of scope (will not match gold): non-AD neurodegeneration unless it's an
      AD-relevant claim about it; epidemiology unrelated to therapeutic targets;
      protocol-design or science-infrastructure claims (those belong in a different
      frontier).
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="spec-back">
    <a class="inline-link" href="/bench">← Back to the leaderboard</a>
    <span class="spec-back__sep">·</span>
    <a class="inline-link" href="/">Browse the gold frontier →</a>
  </p>
</Page>

<style>
  .aside-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .aside-link:hover { color: var(--ink-0); }
  .aside-version {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--ink-4);
    margin-left: 6px;
  }
  div[slot="aside"] {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .inline-link {
    color: var(--signal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
  }

  .spec-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
  }
  .spec-section__title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--size-lg);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-tight);
  }
  .spec-text {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .spec-text code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    padding: 1px 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
  }

  .spec-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .spec-table thead th {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: var(--track-label);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-3);
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .spec-table tbody td {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .spec-table td code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    padding: 1px 4px;
  }
  .spec-table td:last-child {
    text-align: right;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .spec-cmd {
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    padding: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .spec-cmd .tm-ps { color: var(--ink-3); user-select: none; }
  .spec-cmd .tm-cmd { color: var(--ink-0); font-weight: 500; }

  .spec-back {
    margin: var(--space-7) 0 var(--space-5);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .spec-back__sep {
    margin: 0 8px;
    color: var(--ink-4);
  }
</style>
